            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add<strong> </strong>your<strong> rice vinegar</strong> to a small pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, remove from the heat and combine the <strong>vinegar mix</strong> and <strong>cucumber ribbons</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Set them aside to pickle until serving – this is your<strong> quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
